{"type":"step-attempt","step":"spec-review","sessionId":"9d817ae3-a69f-4658-8073-11d1f1a35e8e","outcome":{"verdict":"approved","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/github-merge-gate-determinism/spec-review-result-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":true,"findings":[{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/github-merge-gate-determinism/tasks.md","title":"POST/PUT network error test cases missing from T-08c","rationale":"The spec requirement text says 'SHALL not retry … when a 5xx response is received or a network error is thrown', but T-08c only specifies TC-RC-013 (POST 500) and TC-RC-014 (PUT 502). No test case exercises the catch-block guard that rethrows network errors for POST/PUT. If the implementer misses the catch-block change in T-02, no test would catch it."},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/github-merge-gate-determinism/tasks.md","title":"searchOpenIssuesByLabel cross-origin case absent from T-08h","rationale":"T-07 requires validateSameOrigin to be added to the searchOpenIssuesByLabel pagination loop, but T-08h (TC-SO-001 through TC-SO-005) does not include a cross-origin test for that method. The five-method scope of D7 is not fully exercised by the specified tests."},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/github-merge-gate-determinism/tasks.md","title":"T-03 pseudocode missing .catch() guard on resp.json()","rationale":"The T-03 pseudocode calls resp.json() on the 422 body without a .catch() guard. If GitHub returns a 422 with a non-JSON body (e.g., an HTML error page), an unhandled TypeError propagates instead of GITHUB_API_ERROR. The existing mergePullRequest code already uses .catch(() => ({})) as a defensive pattern."}],"observations":[{"severity":"low","file":"specrunner/changes/github-merge-gate-determinism/request.md","title":"deleteRef referenced in background section does not exist in current codebase","rationale":"request.md mentions 'deleteRef（DELETE, 628行）' as a mutation at risk of duplication, but the method does not exist in src/adapter/github/github-client.ts (confirmed via grep). Line 628 is in listIssueComments. The background section describes an older code state. D2 correctly covers the live DELETE method (removeLabel) which is idempotent — no spec impact."},{"severity":"low","file":"specrunner/changes/github-merge-gate-determinism/tasks.md","title":"T-07 wording conflicts with T-05 pseudocode on initial-URL validation","rationale":"T-07 states 'the initial URL does NOT need to be validated; only Link-header-derived next URLs are validated', but T-05's pseudocode places validateSameOrigin at the top of the while-loop, which also runs on the first (non-Link-derived) URL. The initial URL is constructed from this.baseUrl so the check always passes — harmless but the two paragraphs are in mild tension. No functional impact."}]},"followUpAttempts":1,"transientRetryAttempts":0},"startedAt":"2026-06-26T13:20:33.270Z","endedAt":"2026-06-26T13:27:05.878Z"}
